    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-08-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="110"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 180/77.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chilean Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chilean Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-08-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 17, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With the most profound sorrow I have to discharge
                    the painful duty of informing your excellency that I have this day received from
                    my Government a telegraphic communication announcing to me the <pb facs="0245"
                        n="133" xml:id="pg_133"/> very lamentable demise of His Excellency the
                    President of Chile, Señor Don Pedro Montt, which occurred yesterday at the port
                    of Bremen, Germany, and was caused by heart trouble.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. Yoacham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
